## Why this migration

- The Azure Diagnostics extensions for Windows and Linux (WAD/LAD) are deprecated and retire on **March 31, 2026**. Migration to **Azure Monitor Agent (AMA)** configured by **Data Collection Rules (DCRs)** is a supported option to continue collecting guest OS logs and performance data.
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/azure-monitor-agent-migration-wad-lad
- Guidance also calls out removing WAD/LAD after AMA is configured to avoid duplicate ingestion.
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/diagnostics-extension-overview

---

## Phased approach

### Phase A — Prove AMA + DCR pipeline (non‑SF signals first)

**Goal**: Stand up AMA and minimal DCRs and confirm data lands in **Log Analytics** before tuning for Service Fabric.

#### Exit criteria

- AMA installed and at least one DCR associated (collection starts only after association).
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/azure-monitor-agent-manage
- Log Analytics shows:
    - Windows event logs (`Event` table) via DCR Windows Events collection
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-rule-samples
    - Linux syslog (`Syslog` table) via DCR Syslog collection
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/vm/data-collection-syslog
    - Performance counters (`Perf` table) via DCR performance collection
- DCR processing / transform / delivery errors are not persistent
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-monitor

#### How-to references

- Create DCRs (portal or JSON)
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-rule-create-edit
- DCR JSON samples
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-rule-samples
- AMA install & association options
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/azure-monitor-agent-manage

---

### Phase B — Add Service Fabric signals (inventory → DCR mapping)

**Goal**: Capture which Service Fabric signals are used today and configure DCRs to collect them.

Service Fabric events are available via Windows Event Logs (Windows) and syslog / files (Linux). Platform events are also exposed through EventStore and log channels.

- https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/service-fabric/service-fabric-diagnostics-events

#### Exit criteria

- Inventory worksheet completed
- SF-focused DCRs deployed to a canary scope
- SF signals appear in Log Analytics (`Event`, `Syslog`, `Perf`, or custom tables)
- No persistent DCR ingestion or delivery failures
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-monitor

---

### Phase C — Cutover (remove WAD/LAD)

**Goal**: Remove WAD/LAD once AMA + DCR fully covers required signals.

#### Exit criteria

- WAD/LAD extension removed
- Signals continue via AMA + DCR
- DCR health remains clean
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/data-collection-monitor

