## Appendices

### Appendix A — Service Fabric DCR sample (Windows events)

Service Fabric Windows events are collected from Windows Event Logs and land in the `Event` table.

- Operational event reference:
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/service-fabric/service-fabric-diagnostics-event-generation-operational
- Windows Event Logs via AMA:
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/vm/data-collection-windows-events

**Important**: Use the exact Windows Event Log channel names from Event Viewer.

---

### Appendix B — Application, Reliable Actor, and Stateful Service events

Service Fabric applications and runtimes emit diagnostic events using `EventSource`.

- Application events:
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/service-fabric/service-fabric-how-to-diagnostics-log
- Reliable Actors:
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/service-fabric/service-fabric-reliable-actors-diagnostics
- Reliable Services:
    - https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/service-fabric/service-fabric-reliable-services-diagnostics

EventFlow can be used to route these events to Azure Monitor Logs.

- https://github.com/Azure/diagnostics-eventflow

